@1100 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

Sibel dreamt of her father last night. She claims he urged her to seek out an ancient prison. In its vicinity stands a portal stone that will take us to the Arcanis village at a time when the curse had just befallen it.

The mystery of Sibel's curse continues to produce more questions than answers. Perhaps, we should seek out the monument Sibel speaks of and try to make some sense of the situation.~

@1101 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

Sibel dreamt of her father last night. She claims he urged her to seek out an ancient prison. In its vicinity stands a portal stone that will take us to the Arcanis village at a time when the curse had just befallen it.

The mystery of Sibel's curse continues to produce more questions than answers. The ancient prison might refer to the old stronghold called Watcher's Keep. Perhaps, we should seek out the monument Sibel speaks of and try to make some sense of the situation.~

@1102 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

We have traveled to Watcher's Keep and found the monument Sibel's father spoke of. However, I chose to decline Sibel's offer to travel back in time and witness the unfolding of events at the Arcanis family village. Sibel understood my hesitation and resumed her quest alone. Perhaps, we will meet again.~

@1103 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

We have arrived to Arcanis family village and met with Sibel's great ancestor, Lord Tristan Arcanis. He told us of recent trouble. The great Elm tree grew sick and the quality of leather has dropped. Folk claim it is the gods who have cursed the village, but Lord Arcanis places little trust in these rumours. He asked us to investigate the mystery.~

@1104 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

We have discovered what ails the great Elm tree. A strange apparatus found in the alchemy tower has revealed the culprit - a poison of some kind. We have no clue who may have done the vile deed. Our primary goal is to produce and administer a cure, before it is too late.~

@1105 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

We have made our journey back to Watcher's Keep from Arcanis family village. Our trip borne fruit. Together, Sibel and I have discovered and treated the disease that had caused the suffering of the great Elm tree. The village now may set upon the road to recovery. The mystery of who had poisoned the great tree remains unanswered.~

@1106 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

We have made our journey back to Watcher's Keep from Arcanis family village. Our trip borne fruit. Together, Sibel and I have discovered and treated the disease that had caused the suffering of the great Elm tree. The village now may set upon the road to recovery. The villain behind the scheme turned out to be lord Lawrence Amberville, an old rival of the Arcanis family. We have managed to thwart his attack on the village.~

@1107 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

Sibel's intuition and prowess with the alchemical equipment have guided our efforts in producing and applying the antidote to the diseased roots of the tree. Let us hope the cure works. We should report to Lord Arcanis of our success.~

@1108 = ~Arcanis Family Curse

I have chosen to abandon Sibel's quest and make my way back to Watcher's Keep from Arcanis village. Sibel understood my hesitation and resumed her quest alone. Perhaps, we will meet again.~

@1109 = ~Sibel's Family Dilemma

Sibel received a disturbing letter from lord Lawrence Amberville, the old advirsary of Lord Arcanis. He claims Sibel to be a member of the Amberville family through her mother's line. Furthermore, he warns her of impending treachery from Virtus Arcanis, the only surviving member of the Arcanis family. The story weighs heavily on Sibel's mind. I've no choice but to remain patient as she ponders the given testimony.~

@1110 = ~Sibel's Family Dilemma

Sibel has sought my advice. We took counsel together, and she resolved to maintain her conviction to Arcanis family, no matter what the future may bring.~

@1111 = ~Sibel's Family Dilemma

Sibel has sought my advice. We took counsel together, for there is still doubt that lingers in her mind. I made a promise to stand by her decision when the time comes.~

@1112 = ~Sibel's Family Dilemma

Sibel has sought my advice. We took counsel together, and she chose to refuse whatever offer Virtus Arcanis may bring. Yet she remains skeptical that the mage would ever reveal himself to us.~

@1113 = ~Sibel's Family Dilemma

Sibel has sought my advice. We took counsel together, and she took grave offense to my suggestion that she murders Virtus Arcanis and chose to leave the group instead. I doubt that I will see her again.~

